1
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:19,400
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>[Episode 17]</i>

3
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,400
Mr. Ma.

4
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,200
- President Ma.
- Is A'Yao around?

5
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,400
He's in there. He hasn't gone anywhere.

6
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,400
I'll leave you guys to your work.

7
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,000
Is he the Taoist and failed businessman who lives in the courtyard?

8
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,600
President Ma isn't a monk.

9
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,800
He must be over 50 years old.

10
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,400
He's 40 years old, ten years older than me.

11
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,000
Really?

12
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,200
He's a typical overbearing boss.

13
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,000
He looks old from working too hard.

14
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,500
Let's go.

15
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,600
The oranges need to be roasted a little longer.

16
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,500
Let's have tea first.

17
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,600
- A'Yao.
- Yeah?

18
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:35,788
The money you got from Series A funding is far from enough.

19
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,300
I think it's enough.

20
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:42,000
You're venturing into commerce.

21
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
They're asking you to contribute a portion

22
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,400
so that you'll share the risk.

23
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:50,800
If this goes on,

24
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,800
I'll have to keep selling my apartments.

25
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,400
Do you still have apartments?

26
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,800
Didn't you sell everything in Beijing

27
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,800
to pay off your debts?

28
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,800
These are in my hometown.

29
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,500
In the early years when I made some money,

30
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:10,000
I bought two apartments facing each other for my parents in my hometown.

31
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,800
It was so I would live close to them when I'm back,

32
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,400
and I can take care of them easily.

33
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,700
They were cheap back then.

34
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:19,000
Right now, the prices have gone up significantly.

35
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,000
You have to think this through.

36
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,400
You don't need me to lecture you on investment risks.

37
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,500
You know them better than anyone.

38
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,700
I do.

39
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,500
How should I discuss this with my parents

40
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,900
without causing them distress again?

41
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,100
Let me think about this.

42
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:45,000
You're asking for time to think?

43
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,300
Look at how bold you were back then!

44
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,600
Your parents spent their lives saving money

45
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,500
so that you can buy a small apartment in Beijing.

46
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,400
But what did you do?

47
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,600
You didn't even hesitate in taking the money

48
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,400
to start a business with your classmates.

49
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,900
Well...

50
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,300
A hero won't mention his past glories.

51
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,500
At that time,

52
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,100
I was young and fearless.

53
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,400
Fear didn't exist in my dictionary!

54
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,000
My luck was good as well.

55
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,500
I made money no matter what business I got into.

56
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:14,300
I only spoke to my parents after I earned money.

57
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,000
But at that time,

58
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,100
my parents were proud of me.

59
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,800
All our relatives and neighbors knew about me.

60
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:25,300
Mr. Ma's son has a big company under his name in Beijing.

61
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,300
Everyone asked my parents to pull strings

62
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:30,800
just so their children could get jobs in my company.

63
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,500
At that time...

64
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,600
After that,

65
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,000
when I was down and out,

66
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,500
the same folks began to dish the dirt

67
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,400
and gossip about me.

68
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:52,200
My parents must've felt horrible hearing all this.

69
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,900
Mr. Ma,

70
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:00,500
you've changed so much.

71
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,800
You've learned how to consider your parents' feelings

72
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,600
and even started

73
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,500
to look before you leap.

74
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:12,020
A breathtaking scenery can only be seen at a perilous peak,

75
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,600
but the high and mighty risk the greatest falls.

76
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,600
I'm someone who has fallen from the peak.

77
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,800
It hurts terribly.

78
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,500
I'm scared now.

79
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:26,600
That means you're getting older.

80
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,600
You used to be so young and reckless.

81
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,800
If I didn't invest in your business,

82
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:32,000
you'd point fingers at me and hurl verbal abuse my way.

83
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
"How can you be an investor

84
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,200
with a lack of vision and decisiveness?!"

85
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,600
Well...

86
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,200
Don't slap me in the face.

87
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,300
Leave me some dignity.

88
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,500
That was in the past.

89
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:46,600
Who hasn't been young and reckless before, right?

90
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,900
That's the problem of youth.

91
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:05,900
Hold on.

92
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,400
Granny, you should put this piece here.

93
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,600
You haven't reached the goal yet.

94
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,000
My dice shows five.

95
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,700
I didn't move extra steps.

96
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,800
Granny, you got four.

97
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,900
No, it's five.

98
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,200
You rolled a four.

99
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,200
It's five. I don't care.

100
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,400
My place has reached the goal.

101
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:29,000
Give me the peanuts.

102
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,400
We need to keep a close eye on her.

103
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,900
Granny has picked up bad tricks.

104
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,400
She learned them from you.

105
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,400
I really made a mistake in the last round.

106
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,000
Hurry up.

107
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,800
It's just a game.

108
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:41,300
Don't be angry.

109
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,000
One more time.

110
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,800
Goodness.

111
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:58,462
One, two, three, four. Strike.

112
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,800
Granny, your plane has been sent back to the start.

113
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,000
Two of your planes have been kicked back to the start.

114
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,900
Granny, you aren't angry, are you?

115
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,100
I heard someone say earlier,

116
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:13,000
"It's just a game. Don't be angry."

117
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,400
Granny, ouch!

118
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,100
It hurts!

119
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,400
It's your turn.

