♫ <i>The tower is tall</i> ♫

128
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:58,700
♫ <i>Slim and elegant</i> ♫

129
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:05,000
♫ <i>My baby, time to sleep</i> ♫

130
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,300
Mr. Ma.

131
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:52,000
I wrote a song that fits the tastes of Chairman Xie's dad.

132
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,400
I just completed the melody,

133
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,000
but I haven't had time to draft the lyrics.

134
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,600
You're the first one I'm playing this for.

135
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,200
Listen to it.

136
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,800
Damn it.

137
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,400
What the hell am I even doing here?

138
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,600
I've degenerated.

139
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,300
No.

140
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,000
I need to calm down.

141
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,800
This won't do.

142
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,000
I have to work hard.

143
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,800
♪ <i>Mountain to mountain, cliff to cliff</i> ♪

144
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:45,100
♪ <i>Bees pick flowers from deep in the mountains</i> ♪

145
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:47,200
Blackie! Jiahui!

146
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,200
Hello!

147
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,200
You were diligent for two days.

148
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:57,000
Why are you seated up here again?

149
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,800
Your bulging eyes are scaring people off!

150
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:03,000
Why are you smiling while looking at me?

151
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,800
I've been waiting for you.

152
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,400
Waiting for me?

153
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,000
Why?

154
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,600
I'd like to ask for your advice.

155
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,600
Not again.

156
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,400
You're an elite graduate,

157
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,600
while I'm just an old hag who only went to elementary school.

158
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,000
What help can I offer you?

159
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,200
No, you're wrong.

160
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,700
You possess great wisdom.

161
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,200
Aunty A'Gui, come here.

162
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,200
Please be seated.

163
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,000
All right.

164
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:38,600
Since you've extended a kind invitation, I'll offer a listening ear.

165
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:42,500
Perhaps I'll come up with a good idea or two for you.

166
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,400
There's no rush. Enjoy a cup of tea first.

167
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,100
Thank you.

168
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,000
Here's the thing.

169
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,300
As you know,

170
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:54,500
I'm starting up a business.

171
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,900
Of course,

172
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,800
this isn't my first business venture.

173
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,200
My first few business ventures

174
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:06,400
were rather smooth and successful.

175
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:10,400
I almost reached the peak of my career.

176
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:14,800
However, in the midst of my final venture,

177
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,300
I failed to predict

178
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:19,200
the changes in the market

179
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,000
and went bankrupt.

180
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:28,200
After that, I carefully reflected on my previous successes.

181
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:31,600
I realized that luck played a huge role.

182
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:37,200
As you know, nine out of ten business ventures

183
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,200
are doomed to failure.

184
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:43,600
The risk of failure far supercedes success.

185
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:48,600
Those who can make it to the top are the best in the industry.

186
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:51,400
Well...

187
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:54,200
I do think your past teachings

188
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,600
were absolutely right.

189
00:12:56,600 --> 00:13:00,000
I must take my parents into consideration.

190
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:03,500
My parents are very old now.

191
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:08,400
If I fail again in this venture,

192
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,900
it'll be another terrible blow to them.

193
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:15,200
Here is where my concern lies.

194
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,900
So, I'd like to hear your valuable opinion.

195
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:22,800
Should I start a business again?

196
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,300
Mr. Ma,

197
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:32,000
what you just said is nonsense.

198
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:35,600
Didn't you say that you've ventured into a new business?

199
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,600
Since you've already ventured into a new business,

200
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,800
why are you asking me if you should do it?

201
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,800
Isn't this nonsense?

202
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:46,500
You're right. I didn't make myself clear.

203
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,400
Let me rephrase my question.

204
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:53,200
Should I continue this business venture?

205
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,300
You're asking me whether you should give up halfway.

206
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,800
Right?

207
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:03,800
Fine.

208
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,700
Even if you give up halfway,

209
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:09,000
what are your subsequent plans?

210
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,800
Will you sit here and meditate?

211
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,600
Do you think your current state

212
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:17,600
isn't a terrible blow to your parents?

213
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,800
Meditation is irrelevant to this.

214
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,300
There's an excellent saying in the Sutra of Tranquility.

215
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,200
"If one can maintain a tranquil mind,

216
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,200
even the heavens and earth will reside within them."

217
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:30,000
Don't recite the sutra to me.

218
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,200
Let me ask you this.

219
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,600
You may have a tranquil mind,

220
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,600
but have you thought about your parents?

221
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,000
They might not chide you, but what's on their minds?

222
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,500
Won't they feel anguished?

223
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,100
Won't they be distressed?

224
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,600
Listen up.

225
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:47,000
In my opinion, you might as well strive for your career again.

226
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Strive for something!

227
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,600
Carve out a respectable life.

228
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,600
Only then will your parents be free of worries

229
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,400
about you becoming a monk!

230
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,500
When sparing a thought for your parents,

231
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,800
you have to put yourself in their shoes.

232
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,600
Got it?

233
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:14,600
How can I put myself in their shoes?

234
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:26,000
I have two children.

235
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,000
You know this.

236
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,100
Xiao Xi...

237
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,800
has been close to me since young.

238
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,300
She's always running around me

239
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:43,500
like a puppy, calling, "Mom! Mom!"

240
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:46,000
When she was still in school,

241
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,600
she'd tell me all about happenings in school,

242
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,600
the lessons she attended,

243
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:54,900
their hangouts at a friend's house, and all kind of things

244
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,600
every day once she came home.

245
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,700
Dayang is a boy.

246
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,400
He's tactiturn,

247
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:07,400
but he'd blabber on once you asked him.

248
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,200
So, their dad and I barely worried about them

249
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:15,000
when they were young.

250
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:19,100
No matter what happened, they wouldn't keep secrets from us.

251
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:21,000
They definitely wouldn't.

252
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,300
Things are different now.

253
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,700
They've both grown up.

254
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:34,500
They have their own families and children.

255
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:40,100
We live so far away from them as well.

256
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:45,000
We can only call each other if we want to chat.

257
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,800
Every time I call them, I can only ask,

258
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:49,400
"How have you been?"

259
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,200
"Have you eaten?"

260
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,700
"How's your work?"

261
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:55,100
"How's your health?"

262
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,400
"How's the weather?"

263
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,500
"Are there typhoons?"

264
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,100
They will only answer,

265
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,900
"We've eaten." "We're fine."

266
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:04,800
"Our work is going well."

267
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,200
"We're healthy."

268
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:09,500
Anyway, we only relate good news, not bad ones.

269
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,200
It's all pleasantries.

270
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,500
Gosh.

271
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:14,800
That's true.

272
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,500
My parents ask the same thing.

273
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,700
Without these trivial questions,

274
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:25,200
