412
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,300
I can't stop laughing.

413
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:45,500
It's for you.

414
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:47,100
For me?

415
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:49,200
It's so adorable! Thank you.

416
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:49,880
Thank you!

417
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:50,880
I have more!

418
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:58,000
Damai.

419
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,500
Come here.

420
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,700
Go on.

421
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,600
Who wrote this script?

422
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:49,700
It's written by someone you aren't acquainted with.

423
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:52,200
I admire their courage.

424
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:56,000
Sister, don't you think there's any merit in it?

425
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,400
Yeah, just a little.

426
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,700
What is it?

427
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:01,400
I just said it. Such immense courage.

428
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:07,400
Do you know how to write one?

429
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,500
I don't.

430
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:10,500
Aren't you a novelist?

431
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:11,700
Novels are novels.

432
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:12,500
Scripts are scripts.

433
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,800
These are completely different fields.

434
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,800
Can you step into a different field for once

435
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:19,400
