Let's go.

544
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,580
Xinxin.

545
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:58,558
Candy!

546
00:31:58,558 --> 00:31:59,580
Can I sign up?

547
00:31:59,580 --> 00:32:00,720
Absolutely!

548
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:01,580
How about a few more people?

549
00:32:01,580 --> 00:32:02,860
No problem. Come in.

550
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:05,208
Come inside.

551
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,860
Hello.

552
00:32:07,860 --> 00:32:10,256
These are my friends.

553
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:12,580
Hello.

554
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:29,311
Sunzi went to shoot the sunset on the mountains with her assistant.

555
00:32:29,311 --> 00:32:31,630
They're probably stranded in the rain.

556
00:32:31,630 --> 00:32:34,000
I'm worried their equipment will be damaged by the rain.

557
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,036
That's expensive.

558
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,590
The equipment is fine.

559
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:41,580
They came back when they saw dark clouds.

560
00:32:41,580 --> 00:32:43,940
They're at Huang Xinxin's home right now.

561
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,400
Did Junzi tell you this?

562
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:47,440
Sunzi.

563
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,270
Sorry.

564
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:49,970
Sunzi.

565
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:53,380
Since when were you so chummy with Sunzi?

566
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:57,280
Sunzi asked me to help her come up with ideas.

567
00:32:58,316 --> 00:33:00,390
Why are you so obliging?

568
00:33:02,250 --> 00:33:04,854
I was lured into the cage by her

569
00:33:04,854 --> 00:33:07,636
and got involved somehow.

570
00:33:07,636 --> 00:33:10,140
What do you mean by "lured into the cage"?

571
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:14,440
I was led by the nose.

572
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:18,490
Sunzi speaks in a really affable manner,

573
00:33:18,490 --> 00:33:21,850
so you'll happily be led by the nose.

574
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,620
Hey, Uncle Qingze.

575
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:43,710
Don't worry. I'll be right over.

576
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:45,781
Okay. Bye.

577
00:33:45,781 --> 00:33:46,480
What's wrong?

578
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:47,680
The foal ran off.

579
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,110
The one you witnessed the birth of.

580
00:33:49,110 --> 00:33:50,440
I need to look for it.

581
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:52,960
- I'll go with you.
- Don't come with me. It's raining. Stay here.

582
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:54,890
Lend me an umbrella.

583
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:56,920
The umbrella is useless.

584
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:58,740
Put on my raincoat.

585
00:34:18,670 --> 00:34:21,710
It followed the other horses into another stable.

586
00:34:21,710 --> 00:34:24,860
I searched, but the other horses shielded it from view.

587
00:34:24,860 --> 00:34:26,600
So, I didn't see it.

588
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:30,710
I shouldn't have called you before confirming.

589
00:34:30,710 --> 00:34:32,570
All is well as long as you found it.

590
00:34:32,570 --> 00:34:33,750
Yes, you're right.

591
00:34:33,750 --> 00:34:35,950
You must be freezing.

592
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:37,280
I... I lit a fire in my office.

593
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,510
Warm yourselves up and drink some warm water.

594
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:40,730
Don't catch a cold. Hurry up.

595
00:34:40,730 --> 00:34:42,080
- Okay.
- It's fine.

596
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,830
- I'm really sorry.
- It's okay.

597
00:34:43,830 --> 00:34:46,223
I'll take you upstairs to dry your hair first.

598
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:50,190
The foal didn't go missing,

599
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:52,374
but we almost lost you.

600
00:34:52,374 --> 00:34:54,670
I told you not to wander too far.

601
00:34:54,670 --> 00:34:57,110
Why did you lend the raincoat to someone else?

602
00:34:57,110 --> 00:34:59,486
The tourists had a child with them.

603
00:34:59,486 --> 00:35:00,820
They were stranded there.

604
00:35:00,820 --> 00:35:03,480
Why did you give the umbrella to them, too?

605
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:05,180
There were two children.

606
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:08,960
Goodness.

607
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:12,380
Go closer. Dry yourself first. Don't catch a cold.

608
00:35:16,670 --> 00:35:19,670
Why is it pouring out of the blue?

609
00:35:19,670 --> 00:35:21,166
It's good to have rain.

610
00:35:21,166 --> 00:35:23,214
Mushrooms grow after the rain.

611
00:35:23,214 --> 00:35:25,200
Don't you like to eat mushrooms?

612
00:35:26,670 --> 00:35:27,840
You must be hungry.

613
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:29,190
Here, have some roasted sweet potatoes.

614
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:30,871
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Uncle Zeqing.

615
00:35:30,871 --> 00:35:32,450
Don't be a stranger.

616
00:35:32,450 --> 00:35:34,780
- Have it before it turns cold.
- Okay.

617
00:35:35,630 --> 00:35:37,630
It's hot!

618
00:35:37,630 --> 00:35:39,460
Take it easy.

619
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:42,260
It just came out of the oven.

620
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:47,144
Half have of it first.

621
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:57,040
Why aren't you eating?

622
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:58,700
Thank you.

623
00:35:58,700 --> 00:36:00,700
You're welcome.

624
00:36:01,550 --> 00:36:04,130
Usually, I'm the one who takes care of others.

625
00:36:04,130 --> 00:36:05,730
Are you touched?

626
00:36:05,730 --> 00:36:08,184
Not to that extent.

627
00:36:08,184 --> 00:36:12,180
When I take care of others, they aren't particularly touched.

628
00:36:12,180 --> 00:36:14,400
At most, I'm thankful.

629
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:17,998
Isn't it normal to say you're touched at such a time?

630
00:36:18,930 --> 00:36:23,034
Were you expecting an answer before asking me?

631
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,040
Fine, I'm touched.

632
00:36:27,040 --> 00:36:28,820
I wouldn't dare to feel otherwise.

633
00:36:28,820 --> 00:36:31,860
You're so... Why are you like this?

634
00:36:31,860 --> 00:36:34,461
What a glib talker. What taught you to be this way?

635
00:36:34,461 --> 00:36:36,240
I learned from you.

636
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:39,900
When have I been like this?

637
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:41,260
You've always been like this.

638
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:42,710
I'm not making false accusations.

639
00:36:42,710 --> 00:36:44,510
Granny said

640
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:48,340
when you were in junior high school, you started inviting girls home for meals.

641
00:36:48,340 --> 00:36:49,410
Granny is blabbering nonsense.

642
00:36:49,410 --> 00:36:51,660
When did I invite a girl home for meals?

643
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:54,524
She said the girl ate at your home for over a month.

644
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:57,960
This is triggering some memories.

645
00:36:57,960 --> 00:37:00,130
She was a classmate sitting in front of me.

646
00:37:00,130 --> 00:37:03,070
At that time, her parents went downtown for surgery.

647
00:37:03,070 --> 00:37:04,550
She was left alone at home.

648
00:37:04,550 --> 00:37:07,686
So, I brought her to my house for meals.

649
00:37:09,030 --> 00:37:10,450
How kind-hearted.

650
00:37:10,450 --> 00:37:13,771
Of course. I used to be the vice monitor of our class.

651
00:37:13,771 --> 00:37:15,030
Such a prestigious title.

652
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:16,400
No doubt about that.

653
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,900
What about you?

654
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:23,050
I was our English teacher's assistant.

655
00:37:23,050 --> 00:37:24,440
I'm not asking about that.

656
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:27,660
I'm curious, did you bring boys home for meals?

657
00:37:27,660 --> 00:37:30,200
Surely not.

658
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,840
If I brought a boy home for a meal,

659
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:35,020
my mom would've crippled me.

660
00:37:35,020 --> 00:37:37,070
I'm not talking about your schooling days.

661
00:37:37,070 --> 00:37:42,938
Did you bring your dearest person home for meals?

662
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:48,190
Yes.

663
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:52,000
When my grandma passed away,

664
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:54,030
they applied for leave to accompany me home.

665
00:37:54,030 --> 00:37:55,920
They were a great help,

666
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:57,960
so my family is very fond of them.

667
00:37:57,960 --> 00:37:59,600
They're someone

668
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:02,658
who is extremely likable.

669
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:05,130
Is that person that amazing?

670
00:38:05,130 --> 00:38:06,630
Of course.

671
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:08,286
Couldn't be better.

672
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:10,070
A few words isn't enough to describe them.

673
00:38:10,070 --> 00:38:11,770
I need to

674
00:38:11,770 --> 00:38:14,520
start from our first days in university.

675
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:17,030
You attended the same university?

676
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:19,590
Doesn't that mean you've known each other for more than a decade?

677
00:38:21,150 --> 00:38:24,522
Chen Nanxing and I were classmates at university.

678
00:38:24,522 --> 00:38:25,320
Chen... what?

679
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:26,300
Chen Nanxing.

680
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:27,900
C-H-E-N, Chen.

681
00:38:27,900 --> 00:38:29,880
"Xing" for "North Star".
<i>("Xing" means "star" in Mandarin)</i>

682
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,856
A one and only star.

683
00:38:31,856 --> 00:38:34,772
A one and only star?

684
00:38:34,772 --> 00:38:38,876
Let go of the past.

685
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,930
I'm close to moving on completely.

686
00:38:43,930 --> 00:38:45,460
Look at me.

687
00:38:45,460 --> 00:38:49,920
I can even chat about them with you while eating sweet potatoes.

688
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:52,000
I couldn't do this before.

689
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:55,120
It's like...

690
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:58,398
a cactus thorn in your flesh.

691
00:38:59,860 --> 00:39:02,580
It doesn't disrupt your daily life,

692
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:06,480
but it has a strong presence.

693
00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:10,346
It'll remind you of its existence

694
00:39:10,346 --> 00:39:17,240
no matter... what you do.

695
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:21,140
Do you know what this feels like?

696
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:26,600
I guess I understand

697
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,190
after your analogy.

698
00:39:29,190 --> 00:39:32,282
Once, I went to pick cactus fruit.

699
00:39:32,282 --> 00:39:34,572
A thorn was stuck in my palm.

700
00:39:34,572 --> 00:39:35,480
Whenever I touched it, it hurt.

701
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:38,480
Somehow, I just couldn't get it out.

702
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,780
In the end,

703
00:39:39,780 --> 00:39:41,660
such wounds will recover.

704
00:39:41,660 --> 00:39:47,510
Alternatively, the wound will be inflamed

705
00:39:47,510 --> 00:39:49,590
or suddenly vanish before you realize it.

706
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:56,116
Sometimes,

707
00:39:57,360 --> 00:40:01,160
I think it's good to leave it there.

708
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:08,864
I understand your reluctance to part.

709
00:40:09,550 --> 00:40:11,150
However,

710
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:13,600
there are many instances

711
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:16,610
beyond our own personal control,

712
00:40:16,610 --> 00:40:18,780
let alone the matters of others.

713
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:31,792
In fact, people around us come and go.

714
00:40:32,510 --> 00:40:38,294
Most of the people you meet can only go a short way with you.

715
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:43,068
They'll keep leaving as you walk on.

716
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:48,250
Isn't this what life is like?

717
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:11,024
The rain is never-ending.

